text.section:
Subject to subsections (b) and (c) of this section and except as prohibited under §§ 4-505 and 4-506 of this subtitle, in accordance with the order of priority listed, a member of one of the following classes of individuals who is reasonably available may make an anatomical gift of a decedent's body or part for the purpose of transplantation, therapy, research, or education:
An agent of the decedent at the time of death who could have made an anatomical gift under § 4-503(b) of this subtitle immediately before the decedent's death;
The persons who were acting as the guardians of the decedent at the time of the death of the decedent;
The spouse or domestic partner of the decedent;
The adult children of the decedent;
The parents of the decedent;
The adult siblings of the decedent;
The adult grandchildren of the decedent;
The grandparents of the decedent;
An adult who exhibited special care and concern for the decedent; or
Another person having the authority to dispose of the body of the decedent.
